Showcase on Github
            
Diagram Export Support (v1.2.6 Resolved): - Done
-> PDF: Mermaid diagrams are now rasterized client-side and embedded as high-res images (WYSIWYG).
-> DOCX: Mermaid diagrams are also captured and embedded, with smart sizing and transparency fixes.
-> TODO: Evaluate mermaid-cli for server-side generation (optional optimization).
-> TODO: Implement "Export Pre-processor" hook to substitute JS-widgets with static images.

Missing Diagram Capabilities (GitHub Parity):
-> GeoJSON/TopoJSON Support: Interactive map rendering (Leaflet/MapLibre).
-> STL Support: 3D model viewer (Three.js).

Missing Markdown Features (Audit & Roadmap):
[Navigation & Linking]
-> WikiLinks: Support for `[[Internal Link]]` syntax (Obsidian/Roam standard). - Done (v1.2.6)
-> Header Permalinks: Hover-anchors for all headings (`#` link next to header).
-> Auto-Nav: Previous/Next page links generation based on file order.

[GitHub Compatibility & Extended Syntax]
-> GitHub Alerts: Support for `> [!NOTE]` blockquote syntax (currently we use `!!!` admonitions). - Done (v1.2.6)
-> Mentions: `@username` parsing (useful for future collaboration features).
-> Emoji: `pymdownx.emoji` (:smile:) integration. - Done (v1.2.6)

[Typography & Layout]
-> Smarty: `pymdownx.smarty` for automatic smart quotes, em-dashes, and ellipses. - Done (v1.2.6)
-> Image Resizing: Syntax for `![Alt|100x100](img.png)` or attributes `{: width=100 }`.
-> Captions: HTML5 `<figure>` and `<figcaption>` generation from image titles.
-> Column Layouts: Syntax for multi-column content (e.g., `::: col-2`).

[Academic & Technical]
-> Citations: BibTeX/CSL support for academic referencing `[@author]`.these 
-> Glossary/Abbreviations: Centralized glossary definition and auto-linking. - Done (Extension Enabled)
-> Line Numbers: Toggleable line numbering for code blocks.
-> Data Tables: Sortable/Filterable tables (JS enhancement over static HTML).

[Collaboration]
-> CriticMarkup: Standard formatting for additions `{++ ++}`, deletions `{-- --}`, and comments `{>> <<}`. - Done (v1.2.6)
-> Annotations: Text highlighting `==mark==` with attached comments.

[Advanced Media]
-> Embded PDF/Video: Syntax to embed non-image media directly.
-> Base64 Embedding: `pymdownx.b64` to inline assets for single-file portability.
-> Remote Includes: `pymdownx.snippets` shows in code, but needs config to allow including URLs or relative paths effectively.

Bugs (To Fix in Next Release):
-> Alignment and spacing issue is there when containing Inline Emojis (due to table wrapping logic).
-> Emoji size in Block sections is appearing a bit strecheds.